text:
"Ranoidea robinsonae" is a frog from Papua New Guinea. Scientists saw it in Gulf Province but they think it lives in other places as well. Scientists have only seen this frog in Papua Province, about 750 meters above sea level.
This frog is mostly green in color on the back with pale stripes. The adult male frog is about 2.8 cm long. Some of these frogs have dark spots.
Scientists say this frog is related to the dainty green tree frog.
